Pre-Game Insights: Both Vietnam and Indonesia will eye a comeback in their respective AFC Asian Cup 2023 campaigns.
Vietnam are going to play against Indonesia on 19th January at Abdullah Bin Khalifa Stadium, Doha.
With both teams losing their first match, either side will look to salvage a comeback.
Vietnam's form in all competitions: L-W-L-L-L
Indonesia's form in all competitions: D-L-L-L-L
Nguyen Van Toan stands out as one of Vietnam’s seasoned players, known for his versatility in the forward positions and precise finishing skills.
Witan Sulaeman is Indonesia’s leading active goal-scorer, known for his adaptability and versatility in various roles.
Indonesia have conceded a goal in each of their last five matches.
The last time these two sides met, Vietnam emerged victorious.
Both teams have lost their respective AFC Asian Cup 2023 openers.
There are a couple of injuries in Vietnam camp but Indonesia will come up with a fully fit squad.
Head-to-Head: Total Matches – 16, Vietnam wins – 4, Indonesia wins – 4, Draws – 8
